# However we want to see correlation in graphical representation so below is function for that
def plot_corr(df, size=5):
    corr = df.corr()
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(size, size))
    ax.matshow(corr)
    plt.xticks(range(len(corr.columns)), corr.columns)
    plt.yticks(range(len(corr.columns)), corr.columns)
plot_corr(df)

From the above plot, it is evident that there is no correlation between any 2 columns

# Getting class wise counts to check for target imbalance
n_norm = len(df.loc[df['Class'] == 'Normal'])
n_h = len(df.loc[df['Class'] == 'Type_H'])
n_s = len(df.loc[df['Class'] == 'Type_S'])
total=n_norm + n_h + n_s
print( f'Number of Normal cases: {n_norm}, {round((n_norm / total) * 100) }%' )
print( f'Number of Type H cases: {n_h}, {round((n_h / total) * 100)}%')
print( f'Number of Type s cases: {n_s}, {round((n_s / total) * 100)}%' )

sns.heatmap(df_cm, annot=True);

Confusion Matrix

a. 12, 13 and 15 patients got classified correctly as Normal, Type H and Type S respectively

b. 3 Type H got mis-classified as Normal

c. 8 Normal got mis-classified as Type H

d. 3 Normal got misclassified as Type S

e. Normal class saw maximum mis-classifications

f. Type S class saw no mis-classifications

In [33]:
# automation for finding best k value that gives max accuracy in test data
scores =[]
for k in range(1,50):
    NNH = KNeighborsClassifier(n_neighbors = k, weights = 'distance' )
    NNH.fit(X_train, y_train)
    scores.append(NNH.score(X_test, y_test))

    
print(f'highest accuracy is obtained for k = {np.argmax(scores)+1} with score = {scores[np.argmax(scores)]*100}%')

highest accuracy is obtained for k = 3 with score = 79.62962962962963%

# However we want to see correlation in graphical representation so below is function for that
def plot_corr(df, size=10):
    corr = df.corr()
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(size, size))
    ax.matshow(corr)
    plt.xticks(range(len(corr.columns)), corr.columns)
    plt.yticks(range(len(corr.columns)), corr.columns)
plot_corr(data)

# Detailed suggestions or improvements or on quality, quantity, variety, velocity, veracity etc. on the data points collected by the
# bank to perform a better data analysis in future.
  1. Nan values could be avoided in the target column
  2. more context could be given about the order in columns like level and hidden score (whether lower is better)
  3. columns like highest spend and monthly average spends should be given a scale (whether in thousands, lacs etc ) and also currency
  4. more data could be collected on whether customer previously had a loan
  5. data could be collected on customer is salaried/ self employed
  6. data could be collected on income of the customer
